On Mon, 17 Oct 2005, dan radom wrote:

> i greased it up and set out to install the driveshaft.  the wheel side
> went in pretty easy.  torqued per bentleys and all was well there.  the
> tranny side was much more difficult.

This is another advantage to using the "jack the lower shock attach point"
method.  With some load on the suspension the angle at the transmission
isn't so large and it's easier to get the bolts started.

